Citations
Date:  0/0/1927
Source:  Sheep-Farming, Fencing etc.
Author:  MCKENNY
Vol / Page:  76
Edition:
Quote:  Take out your rule and pencil and mark the scarf that will be required to fit the stay-head to the post. Cut out only what is sufficent to ensure a good grip or catch. This method may be termed 'hubbing' the stay in, or as carpenters call it - 'scribing 'it in.
